PORT ELIZABETH - A Nigerian televangelist is due back in the Port Elizabeth magistrate's court where he faces charges of human trafficking and rape.
	
	The pastor will appear in the dock alongside three women, who allegedly helped the pastor recruit girls, for the purposes of sexual exploitation. He is accused of trafficking over 30 girls and women, from various branches of his church, between 2012 and 2016. READ:Â Third alleged recruiter for human trafficking pastor arrested The state says some of the alleged victims are as young as 13. The case is expected to be transferred to the high court in Port Elizabeth. The trial is set for July. eNCA